        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 12:48PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1247 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Nadine, or 13 miles east of Hobbs, moving southeast at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Lea,
northwestern Andrews and southwestern Gaines Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
